DataTable COMPONENT

  - Element UI's Table component used
  - Props used for Configuration and Show some data.
  	* refName - defines the table referance id
  	* columns - defines the table columns visibility, align, type etc
  	* table - table data used in rows
  	* title - defines table cards title, icon etc
  	* countRow - defines how many rows will show on one page
  	* pageSizes - defines row count option will show on the page (5-10-25-50-100)
  	* defaultSort - default sorting option with which column
  	* selectable - defines rows are selectable
  	* filterable - defines rows are filterable
  	* options - defines table settings is on or off (show-hide columns and freeze popup)
  	* rowActions - defines row actions on one row
  	* addUsers - defines (+) icon and tell how should it be (like pop-up or dropdown menu)
  	* empty - defines empty status of the table
  	* selectEvent - defines multiple selectEvents actions or dropdown inside dropdown.
  	* chartOptions - defines if a chart added to table how it should look like.

  - When you want use this component just import it anywhere and don't forget the configuration of required props.
  - Methods defined for what is used for, you can add more on that
  - <el-table-column> attributes defines the table; show, type etc.
  - You can add more columns if needed. Just don't forget this component used on all project.
  - You can use elTableRef as a referance of the table.
  - Also we have to Watch some data changes and response on the table. When you are implementing to a new one please consider the side effects of the component.

For furhter things please read the documentation of the Element UI
